The Proposal: -

Washim district. Brahmanwada B. The original budget of Ta Malegaon Tap Water Supply Scheme was prepared by CEO, Zilla Parishad, Washim vide Reference No. Technical approval is provided under Section 2. Also, Reference No. Under Section 1, a nominal price of Rs 22,68,469 / - is granted by the Administrator. Also, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Washim proposed to give revised administrative approval to the proposed tap water supply scheme vide Reference Letter No. 4 here. The letter dated 14.11.2024 has been submitted to the government. Reference No. 3 here. Under the letter dated 14.11.2024, the government was considering granting revised administrative approval to the price as per the revised technical approval given by the Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Washim.
The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Md. Brahmanwada B.T. The scheme of the Malegaon Tap Water Supply Scheme has been given a price hike of Rs. The revised price of 22,98,071 / - (Rupees twenty-two lakhs ASAT thousand seventy-one only) is being approved by the Administrator.
Government Decision No: Suprama-2024 / P.No.526 / Papu 93 (Office No.897991)
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred every year for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), reduction in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) A CAG report in 2013 shows that 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills. In fact, in order to make the scheme financially viable, it will be the responsibility of the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad to increase the water tariff as per requirement.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.

9) Since administrative expenditure is not permissible under the Jal Jeevan Mission, it should be excluded if any administrative expenditure of 4% has been taken up in the revised budget of the scheme.
